        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>And if none of the hundreds of thousands of flights leaving American airports each year turn into Paris, 1848, that is to the lasting credit of Skymall, a thing of genius and the work of superior minds, the most significant class-pacification device of our times.</p>
<p>Social harmony: Priceless.</p>
<p><em>Rob Goodman is a Trinity senior. His column appears Fridays.</em></p>

